      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 44: The constructor only validates increaseRampTime, but setLimits() accepts and normalizes min/max while Config construction does not. If a caller provides Config{.minBitrateKbps \u003e .maxBitrateKbps}, later std::clamp() calls have an invalid range, which is undefined behavior. Normalize limits in the constructor before any clamping can occur.\n```suggestion\nBandwidthController::BandwidthController(const Config\u0026 cfg)\n    : cfg_(cfg)\n    , targetBitrate_(cfg.initialBitrateKbps)\n    , lastStableBitrate_(cfg.initialBitrateKbps)\n{\n    if (cfg_.minBitrateKbps \u003e cfg_.maxBitrateKbps)\n        std::swap(cfg_.minBitrateKbps, cfg_.maxBitrateKbps);\n    if (cfg_.increaseRampTime \u003c\u003d 0.0f)\n        cfg_.increaseRampTime \u003d 10.0f;\n    targetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(targetBitrate_);\n    lastStableBitrate_ \u003d targetBitrate_;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "ff7ddd68882e789c531a9b558353a63d5974907a",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
