      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 110: applyDecrease() can turn a malformed maxDecreaseFactor into an increase or an underflowed unsigned value. Config is public and only partially validated, so values outside [0,1] can produce factor \u003e 1, factor \u003c 0, or a negative lround() cast to unsigned before clampBitrate(). Clamp the configured factors once in the constructor or locally before use.\n```suggestion\ncfg_.maxDecreaseFactor \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.maxDecreaseFactor, 0.0f, 1.0f);\ncfg_.minIncreaseFactor \u003d std::max(cfg_.minIncreaseFactor, 0.0f);\ncfg_.maxIncreaseFactor \u003d std::max(cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor, cfg_.minIncreaseFactor);\ncfg_.audioReductionFactor \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.audioReductionFactor, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n```",
