      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 692: setNewBitrate() now sets lastMediaRestart_ every time the controller changes bitrate. adaptQualityAndBitrate() then ignores RR feedback for 2 seconds after each change, while the controller\u0027s normal probing interval is 1 second. During probing this can suppress the loss/RTT signal after every increase, allowing consecutive increases based mainly on REMB-normal feedback before RR congestion is considered. Keep a separate encoder-restart/stale-report timestamp, or only suppress RR after actual encoder restarts rather than every bitrate adjustment.\n```suggestion\n// Only update the stale-report guard when the encoder is actually restarted/reconfigured,\n// not for every target bitrate change.\n```",
